caption: Great sushi/Thai location right next to the Georgia Ave. Metro stop. For two, we usually get their "sushi deluxe set C" with a noodle or rice entree. Their take-away is prepared as fresh/right-before-you-arrive as possible, which makes this place a repeat choice for us every few months. Worth a visit!
Definitely one of the tastier eateries in DC. The food is fresh and wholesome and I think they use natural herbs and spices to flavour their food - no MSG!

I cannot believe we haven't left a review before, as we eat here often. Pre-pandemic, we loved eating here in-person because it is absolutely charming inside. The vibe/environment they've created is adorable and cozy, and the market they have is fabulous. They were also always so nice about us having our baby (and later, toddler) with us—and it's often hard to find spots that are friendly with little kids.  During the pandemic, we've ordered delivery from here several times and not only is the sushi delicious, but it always arrives SO BEAUTIFULLY presented. We've never received sushi for delivery that looks so well presented from anywhere else. Highly recommend Pantry Thai!

Beautiful interior and delicious food -- can't go wrong with any of the noodle or curry dishes. There's also a nice little market inside with all kinds of Asian cooking staples. I bought a few different curry pastes that I had never been able to find in the standard grocery stores.
Great dumplings and affordable 🙂
WOW, delicious. 5/5 stars.

From the first moment  you enter that restaurant  team give you a great feeling. Very comfortable team, it is a good place to to go out with friends and colleagues or with your date. tasty  food, qualified  chef de cuisine, modest  pay and professional  service. Highly recommended.
I love it

Great service and crew, I had house salad and really liked the peanut dressing. I also had nagiri salmon and tuna, both really nice. I hope COVID ends and we go back to silverware instead of plastics forks and straws.

I haven't tasted the food yet. Kinda scared to. Delivery is awful the guy called asking for a tip before he even arrived. I called to cancel they said they couldn't. He delivered the food smelling like liquor.
Good Thai Food at decent prices.

I’ve gotten delivery from here many times and everything has always been very good. They make both Thai food and sushi well. The prices are reasonable for the quality and quantity (by DC standards). Everything is always packed well and delivered quickly. Great neighborhood spot!

I experienced the best customer service. My server was most kind and considerate. When she came to check on me and I complained that there were too many flies on the patio where I was dining, she left, then returned later with a can of Deep Woods OFF. I'll assume that she had received complaints from other patrons, who have dined on the patio. It really is the simple things, done well, which fosters great customer service experiences. Bravo!
The Rainbow sushi and shrimp pad thai is the best in town. They also took every precaution to ensure that they followed CDC guidelines for Covid-Virus. I felt safe eating there.
My favorite Thai in DC.
Contactless pick up was great! I've enjoyed the sushi the last few times we've ordered pick up!
Food is good
Great sushi and love the seaweed salad! Easy and safe pickup
I am so bummed this restaurant is closed and hoping it is just temporary!!! The sushi is wonderful and they are a highlight of living in the neighborhood.
The sushi is ridiculously fresh!
There chicken pad Thai is always a go to takeout meal!
Nice products
the food was delicious and the service wonderful

Great vibe. Delicious food. The dumplings are fantastic, they are unique with a meatloaf style filling that's savory and juicy. My pad Thai was excellent. A bit too spicy for my girlfriend so I recommend most people should ask for mild spicy if you choose the spicy option. The sake selection is also wonderful. I will definitely be going back.
Delicious variety of Asian fusion, quick, spacious, and good service

I really like this place. I love spicy food and just happened to stop in. I got an wonderful seafood meal and two sodas for less than $26. It's quaint and very good service. It's right at the Petworth Metro station.
Lovely food and very generous portions. Really enjoyed my calamari and pad see ew.
The best Happy Hour! Food is spicy and delicious. I hate the way the staff stares at you while sitting at the bar...Please stop doing that.
Food is great. Service and servers are TERRIBLE. So go enjoy the food and if service is bad dont be surprised.
It's okay but the picture they have none of the stuff on the advertisement they have nothing just regular orders

At the moment  you come to that restaurant  team give you a great feeling. Very comfortable stuff, it is a lovely restaurant to hang out with friends and colleagues or with your date. Great  meals, qualified  chef, modest  price and attentive  service. Warmly recommended.
Racist will never eat from them again. Probably the worse 20$ I’ve ever spent. Wish I didn’t have to put a star they would get a big fat zero.
Very nice staff.
Delicious
ka prow chicken bento is 🔥 and affordable
Good food, service, presentation, and atmosphere. We really enjoyed our dinner here.
The lunch bento box was amazing.

Delicious Thai food, and not super spicy.  Tried a few different things on the menu and everything was very fragrant and full of flavor, the basil is very aromatic.  Atmosphere was very calming and relaxing and the staff was polite and attentive.  Cost isn't too bad either, for 2 entrees a salad and soup the total come to about $41.

Pad Thai with chicken was fresh and well portioned. Nice location and style. The indie rock music inside took away from the calm ambiance. I’ll revisit and sit outside when the weather is nice or order pick up since it’s near the metro.

in all honesty, the food was amazing. the aura was calming and serene. the inside and outside are both very beautiful. it's pretty obvious what they have, so you can't go there and be disappointed with what they serve. the service is amazing as well! the servers are kind and respectful, and i think this place deserves a 5 star rating.
(Translated by Google) One of my favorite places in DC. Good food and a good price  (Original) Uno de mis lugares favoritos en DC. Buena comida y a buen precio

I’m fairly new to the neighborhood and I am a foody so I love trying new spots. I just stopped in to grab some sushi before I got home and had a bad experience with one of your waitresses, Jenny.  I walked in, wasn’t greeted which wasn’t that big, but I looked for the closest menu. Just so happen, I saw menus sitting at the bar to the side of a patron who was already indulging in his food. I picked up the menu to quickly scan what I needed and Jenny, who didn’t greet me or offer a menu, literally snatched it out of my hand saying it was the guys, that had already ordered and had them sitting to the side of him on the bar top, menu. That was extremely embarrassing unprofessional and uncalled for. Even the man at the bar said it was okay because he had already ordered.  Her customers service is extremely poor. It’s safe to say, I will not be stopping by again.
Good food. Nice space.
Very solid Thai and sushi

I'm always skeptical of "pan-cultural" restaurants. It's incredibly difficult to cater to serve such disparate cuisines as Thai, Korean and Japanese, but not impossible. Pantry proves this. All reasonably priced too. I have not tried any of the liquid offerings, but I've heard good things on that front too.
Great food for the money

Absolutely amazing service and food. My wife and I order from these guys all the time. I’m a big fan of their drunken noodles and my wife loves their sushi rolls. The customer service is also fantastic. If I ever have any issue with anything, they make sure they fix it. I highly recommend you check this place out and support your local businesses.
Relaxed atmosphere, exceptional service, great prices, beautifully prepared & delicious food. I always come back to Pantry for happy hour and Sunday brunch. BY FAR the best place for sushi in DC!

Love this place! Great thai food and sushi. The noodles and stir fry are excellent. Recommend ordering extra veggies with the curry as they often don't come with many. They also sell some ingredients and cooking supplies to make thai food at home.
Great experience, beautiful decor, I bought a candle. The sushi was delicious and the steamed dumplings were yum-yum!!

One of the best lunch deals in Petworth. The Ka Prow bento box is something like $12, but you get miso soup, two spring rolls, rice, and a heaping pile of minced chicken (or other meats if you prefer). It's a staple in a pretty dry part of town as far as lunch options.
It was excellent. The green curry has an addictive quality. I had a fried sushi roll that was the only one I've ever really liked. The eggplant was also crazy good. I really like the decor too.
Incredible thai food and sushi! It’s rare to find both in the same place. Not to mention the market selection is interesting and good as well.
Spicy papaya salad was great and the service was great too
Good food and service
Good

I love this place! I find the food really good and the prices are right. Great service and such a cute spot- great decor! I'm shocked it's not packed more often.  Also, awesome place to have a solo dinner at the bar. I've had the green curry and the drunken noodles there. Both were really good.
Love your happy hour prices and extraordinary food!

The Pad Thai is outstanding. It is so fresh, zesty and delicious. It was ready in less than fifteen minutes and the woman who took my order was extremely sweet. I was given water while I waited and the atmosphere is so cute. I will definitely be going back here!!
Great food at surprisingly good prices for the area.  Also, they have two types of unfiltered sake!
Great sushi! The service was respectful & helpful. Nice atmosphere & clean.
Fast and friendly
I am so lucky this place is in my neighborhood! I can stop by on my way home to pick up some delicious food. Staff very friendly and hospitable, even when I'm taking something to go.
Always yummy!

Prices are actually pretty decent from what I expected... I read the reviews and had to try the chicken Pad Thai! It was honestly delish, flavor was perfect!! Also had the shrimp tempura roll, really good as well!
Good ..
Eel roll literally only had eel skin in it .

Stopped by for one of my favorite menu items the chicken pad thai no bean sprouts. Service is always friendly and fast. You can grab a drink at the bar if you're ordering to go. Love the decor. The sushi is also really good.
Consistently amazing with everything I have tried. Chicken Ka Prow, Drunken Noodles, Panang Curry, Pad See Ew. All of it
Great happy hour for the locals. Never crowded and quick service.

The food here is amazing. It’s primarily Thai food, but they have great sushi and some other Asian inspired dishes as well. This is where Sala Thai used to be, but the decor is completely different now. It feels like a trendy new American restaurant with lots of clean lines, open space and a little market in the back with specialty food items, some things you would find in an Asian grocery store and others in a high end shop with ceramics and interesting condiments.
I just moved back from Thailand after two years and this place is spot on!  Food and environment is excellent.  Pad Thai and Drunken noodles are fantastic!

This place is so affordable and phenomenal. The environment was divine. The lightning was pleasant. The music was exciting but not over bearing. If you’re in the D.C. area, you have got to try this restaurant!
I support this good  Thai restaurant.
That's the right flavaz
Wonderful, for my first time...  family friendly and nice for dinning solo. I'll visit again and recommend
Food was excellent. Pad Thai had tons of flavor, also highly recommend the calamari. Service was great and will definitely be back.
Food is spectacular. The Happy Hour is by far the best in the city. Mojitos are a must!!!!!!
Try their noodles!

The soup dishes are not satisfying, they're either too bland (like the ramen) or too salty (like the wonton soup). And the traditional Thai dishes like Pad Thai just don't have the right flavor. However the appetizers are good, like the crab rangoon and or the wings. The sushi haven't disappoint, and I recommend the volcano roll (pictured), their version of the rainbow roll, or any of the classic rolls. The drinks are great too, like the ginger mojito (pictured), the lychee martini, or the great (though small) selection of sake.
Pad Thai, crab rangoon, and chicken pineapple are great!
pretty good local thai/sushi
Great food, friendly staff
A yet to be discovered gem with an  interesting selection of dishes. While they advertise Thai, one of their best dishes is a Japanese-style ramen noodle soup.
Great place to dine. The ambiance is lovely and the food is very reasonably priced and tasty. They have a selection of very nice drinks too and a bar area.
Awesome place everything they sell is cheap as hell
Good food good sushi definitely come back again👍😄
I love this place. Prices were great and service was amazing. I will come back.
Love this place! Very friendly staff and helpful to the highest degree.
Wonderful and fast service, delicious food, and the 5-7:30pm happy hour prices are great!
Sorry i never been to the Pantry, i thought this post was for Bread for the City.

This Thai place is beautiful inside, and I love the food. The service is good, fast, friendly, and humble. I feel that many people overlook this gem, and they really should come out, more. You get a great dining experience for the price!
Todd make very spicy shrimps not for the faint of heart! Very friendly bartender not so crowded so good service
Some things have gotten better others are worse but it's the only thai option in the neighborhood so they've got it covered
Convenient, good, comfort food. Haven't tried the sushi.
The food was fantastic and the service was top notch and prices were reasonable.

At first sight the decor is modernly eclectic and peaceful. The service was great. The food.. we are travelers and I can honestly say that this is probably one of the best restaraunts I've ever eaten at in my life. I expected average Thai. We ordered the Larb Gai, Pad See Ew, Kyushu Ramen, bento box, and various other items. I was blown away at the flavors they were able to add into the simple sounding dishes. Everything from the house salad to the ramen was meticulously executed with only an expert pallet. I HIGHLY recommend choosing The Pantry when in DC for the BEST THAI FOOD EVER!!
Came for take out and a drink. I had the dark and stormy nothing fancy.
Best Drunken noodles in D.C.
surprisingly great. Near Petworth subway.
Great food, great staff
The sushi is great. Very good service and the drinks are great. A hidden treasure I definitely recommend this restaurant
Thus has been my favorite little lunch spot for last week...great service tasty food from sushi to Asian style wings and the best green tea ice cream! Great wait staff as well
Our go-to Thai restaurant. The Fed Curry and Pad Thai are wonderful.
It's sort of tough to mess up Thai dishes but somehow these guys did it. The portions are also small with very little meat esp for the high price
Really good sushi and miso soup . Really clean place
Had an amazing meal here. They have great happy hour specials, food is excellent, and the service is really good. All of their sushi is particularly good and you should try the Pad see eew!
Greatly improved atmosphere and food. I'm not sure why it isn't busier yet in a part of the neighborhood lacking restaurants. The happy hour specials are very well priced

This is my go to place to order food. It's like a hidden gem in my list of takeout places. The sushi here is pretty good (I actually was not expecting it to be this good). I only wish they started selling it earlier than 4pm. Thai food here is also good, particularly the drunken noodles(I also was not expecting that). A hidden gem in the heart of Petworth. It's  not mind blowing but great for the price you are paying.
